WEBVTT

00:01.058 --> 00:04.262
This lecture is brought to you by Beauford Road Baptist Church.

00:04.682 --> 00:07.065
The speaker today is Pastor David Kogel.

00:08.167 --> 00:09.548
We start a new series.

00:09.769 --> 00:11.591
If you remember, we finished up on Jonah.

00:13.614 --> 00:16.918
The Lord kind of led me to this series of on prayer.

00:18.740 --> 00:30.194
And what I hope to do is give you a few introduction lessons that kind of deal with as far as getting ourselves

00:30.274 --> 00:37.725
in the position to pray as we should, thinking about what the Word says about prayer.

00:38.566 --> 00:45.075
And some different things that will help, I believe you and me as we go to the Lord in prayer.

00:46.578 --> 00:58.034
And also as we finish these introductory lessons, then I really want to get into what I had originally thought I originally had is what happened when they prayed.

00:58.562 --> 01:05.910
being people through the Bible when we see specific places where they prayed for something.

01:06.431 --> 01:08.773
They really got down business in prayer.

01:09.534 --> 01:10.655
And what took place?

01:10.755 --> 01:12.317
What happened?

01:12.337 --> 01:18.043
And looking at those individual things as we go along, I think will help us as well.

01:19.325 --> 01:27.634
We want to look at some things that are techniques according to biblical standards and things that can help us

01:28.034 --> 01:29.956
as we go to the Lord in prayer.

01:31.077 --> 01:33.319
Prayer is such a great tool.

01:33.639 --> 01:43.589
It's our way to communicate to the Lord and tell Him what's on our heart and what we're looking answer for to prayer.

01:43.749 --> 01:51.677
And we want to look at why maybe some people are not getting answers to prayer, why people are not praying even.

01:52.357 --> 01:57.042
And so we want to look at those as well.

01:57.250 --> 02:02.336
I'll use a little key verse to start off with 1 Thessalonians 5, 17.

02:03.237 --> 02:09.765
And you know that that's just a simple three word, pray without ceasing.

02:10.667 --> 02:11.768
Pray without ceasing.

02:12.749 --> 02:19.658
And as we look at that verse, you may say, well, how can I do that?

02:21.059 --> 02:23.062
How is that possible?

02:23.082 --> 02:26.386
Because I think many times when we think about prayer,

02:26.530 --> 02:30.254
we think about getting down on our knees and praying.

02:30.414 --> 02:31.575
And that's true.

02:31.656 --> 02:32.857
We do that many times.

02:32.917 --> 02:34.178
Folks come to the altar.

02:34.819 --> 02:37.702
It's always good to see folks come to the altar and pray.

02:38.943 --> 02:47.573
We have people that have had a prayer meeting this morning and every Sunday morning out there and at nine o'clock and they're praying.

02:48.173 --> 02:56.082
But you know, one thing about it, when it says pray without ceasing, God doesn't mean that we have to fall down on our knees

02:57.090 --> 02:59.093
everywhere all the time and pray.

02:59.734 --> 03:02.638
You know, I do a lot of praying, standing up.

03:02.658 --> 03:04.541
I do a lot of praying, sitting somewhere.

03:04.901 --> 03:06.523
I do praying, going down the road.

03:07.545 --> 03:11.450
You know, there's many times that we're, we're praying.

03:11.530 --> 03:16.517
And so what that means is we should be in a spirit of prayer.

03:17.519 --> 03:21.745
Well, we engage through all these duties that we do on earth.

03:22.526 --> 03:25.490
Prayer can be without ceasing in the heart.

03:26.562 --> 03:33.452
And I believe we need to realize that our heart is full of the presence of God and we're communing with Him.

03:34.274 --> 03:37.879
You know, when I get up in the morning, I want to talk to the Lord.

03:37.939 --> 03:39.401
I want the Lord to speak to me.

03:39.421 --> 03:49.236
And so we're communing with the Lord in prayer and why shouldn't we just carry that on as we go about our daily duties and doing things in life.

03:50.037 --> 03:55.826
So that's really what that verse is trying to tell us that we can pray without ceasing.

03:56.770 --> 04:11.369
Now, there are some biblical techniques and I'm not trying to get technical with you here and things like that, but we are, we are going to have a, I know you do and I know I do want to have a satisfied prayer life.

04:12.191 --> 04:17.778
I want to feel like when I pray that I'm praying as I should,

04:18.402 --> 04:23.409
I'm looking, God is listening to me and I'm looking to God to answer some prayers.

04:23.509 --> 04:29.136
And so these are things that we hope will happen as we go to the Lord in prayer.

04:30.098 --> 04:48.242
So what this does is gives you a spiritual heart checkup because if we make sure that things are right on the inside when we go to the Lord in prayer and we think about some of these things that we can do, I believe you'll see much more

04:48.546 --> 04:52.931
You'll see different, you'll feel more satisfied about your praying.

04:53.692 --> 04:55.474
You'll know that the Lord is listening.

04:56.135 --> 05:06.488
All of these things, if we do that spiritual checkup, so I have like six conditions here about a satisfied prayer life.

05:07.169 --> 05:11.754
God's word and prayer, they work hand in hand.

05:13.136 --> 05:14.958
By word, have I hid in my heart?

05:15.739 --> 05:18.002
And that's going to make a difference when you pray.

05:18.658 --> 05:21.241
It's going to make a difference as you go to the Lord in prayer.

05:22.342 --> 05:27.087
And because, you know, you and I are going to face so many heartaches in this life.

05:28.148 --> 05:38.819
And when heartaches come, when things happen to us and around us and our families, whether it be our children or grandchildren, we watch them would maybe go down the wrong path.

05:38.879 --> 05:41.562
We see them make bad decisions.

05:42.143 --> 05:45.426
And we think about, hey, you know, I did the same thing when I was young.

05:46.370 --> 05:50.075
And I know my mom and dad prayed for me every day.

05:51.196 --> 05:52.958
And I thank the Lord for that.

05:53.679 --> 06:03.251
But as we think about all these things that are happening all around us, we want to see answers to these prayers.

06:04.453 --> 06:10.560
But I think for many folks, their prayer life becomes weakened along the way.

06:10.600 --> 06:13.404
Maybe they didn't get answers as soon as they thought they should.

06:13.464 --> 06:15.186
Maybe

06:15.266 --> 06:19.190
They didn't really believe God was going to do something when they prayed.

06:20.352 --> 06:25.397
And that sometimes makes shows up a lacking prayer life after that.

06:25.998 --> 06:28.721
Because they just give up.

06:28.741 --> 06:31.444
I've talked to people who said, I've been praying and praying and praying.

06:31.824 --> 06:34.708
And there's just no answer for this thing I'm praying for.

06:35.048 --> 06:36.089
I'm just going to give up.

06:37.991 --> 06:44.178
And so we want to think about some of the things that we can do to help those along.

06:44.770 --> 06:49.195
how to pray, how to enter into that prayer attitude.

06:49.716 --> 06:54.581
You see, prayer is something, and this is how a lot of people feel about it.

06:54.601 --> 07:00.969
They feel that prayer is something we pretend to do because we are religious people and we're supposed to do it.

07:02.110 --> 07:04.993
That's the thinking of a lot of people.

07:05.013 --> 07:12.562
Well, you know, I'm a religious person and I go to church, and so therefore I know that, you know, I'm supposed to pray,

07:14.274 --> 07:16.958
But it really goes a whole lot deeper than that.

07:19.102 --> 07:25.172
I remember it's been quite a while back, Carrie Underwood, sang a song and said, Jesus, take the wheel.

07:26.735 --> 07:27.596
And I like that.

07:28.838 --> 07:31.723
But I'm getting to think a little bit more about that thing better yet.

07:31.883 --> 07:35.890
It's better if we let Christ stay on the wheel all the time.

07:36.898 --> 07:44.167
You see, it's not, well, I've been working at it and I've been doing this and I'm struggling through that and I really can't get any further.

07:44.528 --> 07:47.091
Jesus, will you come over here and take the wheel now?

07:47.952 --> 07:49.053
Will you take over now?

07:50.335 --> 07:52.518
Why not let him take over all the time?

07:53.679 --> 07:57.424
Why not let him be there all the time at the wheel?

07:57.444 --> 08:00.508
And then when things happen, you know that he's right there.

08:00.568 --> 08:03.832
You've already given it to him, turned it over to him.

08:03.912 --> 08:05.554
You're trusting in him.

08:07.330 --> 08:15.180
So we need to realize when we look at that pray without ceasing, it means being prayer continually.

08:15.740 --> 08:18.604
It's something that we got to work at continually.

08:20.426 --> 08:32.060
I don't know if you know anybody that's much into bodybuilding, but these guys and girls that really get out there and go to the gym day in, day out, never miss a time.

08:32.621 --> 08:36.786
I mean, they're working, they're continually disciplined themselves.

08:37.506 --> 08:39.889
It doesn't matter what kind of conditions outside.

08:39.909 --> 08:41.130
They're going to make it to the gym.

08:41.190 --> 08:42.451
It doesn't matter how they're hurting.

08:42.471 --> 08:43.272
They're going to get there.

08:43.292 --> 08:44.213
They're going to work out.

08:44.253 --> 08:45.555
They're going to stay in good shape.

08:46.095 --> 08:48.999
You know why they're building that body for something.

08:49.920 --> 08:51.321
That's just what they want to do.

08:53.323 --> 08:54.625
And I begin to think about that.

08:55.065 --> 09:06.578
We as Christians have to work on our heart muscles as well, continue to build that prayer life, continue to be firm about it.

09:07.074 --> 09:10.397
Don't say, well, I just don't feel like praying today.

09:11.258 --> 09:16.684
Well, I don't feel like I'll talk to the Lord that much today.

09:16.724 --> 09:17.765
I got a lot else to do.

09:18.246 --> 09:31.039
We're never gonna get that prayer life that we need to have if we don't constantly, continually working that heart muscle and talking to the Lord.

09:31.600 --> 09:33.682
It doesn't have to be long prayers.

09:34.690 --> 09:39.715
There are times when we spend a lot of time, we're pouring out our heart to the Lord.

09:39.735 --> 09:42.097
We're telling them all these things that are happening.

09:42.118 --> 09:42.658
It's good.

09:44.059 --> 09:47.923
But there are times when we just need to thank you, Lord, for blessing me today.

09:47.963 --> 09:51.687
Thank you, Lord, for being with me today.

09:51.707 --> 09:59.795
I mean, but at least because we're in that attitude or prayer and we own that terms, we should be with the Lord.

09:59.855 --> 10:02.418
We don't mind talking to the Lord like that.

10:03.906 --> 10:05.168
And that's the way it should be.

10:06.490 --> 10:08.734
Let me ask you this pondering question.

10:09.295 --> 10:14.624
Does God promise to answer everyone's prayer?

10:16.227 --> 10:19.652
Does He promise to answer everyone's prayer?

10:20.374 --> 10:21.255
You think about that.

10:22.978 --> 10:30.130
Because as we get into these things that we need to be at, things that we need to do when we pray,

10:30.722 --> 10:34.566
There are reasons why we don't see answers to some prayers.

10:35.267 --> 10:36.708
There are some things happening.

10:37.990 --> 10:45.358
And we just can't expect God to be a genie that we've rubbed the lamp and say, God, now I need you right now.

10:45.398 --> 10:46.459
Come on in answer, Rick.

10:48.782 --> 10:50.523
Are we in the place where we should be?

10:52.145 --> 10:54.288
Let's get John 15, seven.

10:55.569 --> 11:00.274
I tried to stay away from John pastor because I know you're teaching on that, but it's heartache.

11:00.546 --> 11:02.428
to get out a few verses out of there.

11:04.170 --> 11:14.562
But this first technique, number one on your page there, is a technique to apply is an honest heart before God.

11:15.322 --> 11:18.446
Is your heart honest before God?

11:19.707 --> 11:29.458
And what I mean by that, he tells us in John 15, seven, if you abide in me and my words abide in you,

11:30.242 --> 11:33.966
ye shall ask what you will, and it shall be done unto you."

11:33.986 --> 11:37.550
Now, a lot of folks love that last phrase.

11:37.570 --> 11:43.976
They just love to pluck that out of there and say, well, the Bible says, ask what you will, and it'll be done unto you.

11:44.777 --> 11:47.200
But they don't want to do what the first part does.

11:47.460 --> 11:52.625
They don't want to think about that because we have to be abiding in the Lord.

11:52.685 --> 11:57.010
And remember how I said the Word of God works hand in hand with prayer?

11:57.378 --> 12:01.763
We have to abide in him and his words abide in us.

12:03.325 --> 12:04.767
So it's very important.

12:04.827 --> 12:07.630
It's an awesome biblical truth to cling to here.

12:08.832 --> 12:10.534
We have to remain in him.

12:10.554 --> 12:14.819
We have to buy the word that's being given to you and me.

12:14.859 --> 12:18.623
And we ought to, we need to use that word.

12:19.224 --> 12:24.530
It's been well said, but in scripture, every promise has a condition and a premises.

12:25.634 --> 12:26.535
You know what that means?

12:26.735 --> 12:29.679
That means, yes, it promises there.

12:29.939 --> 12:30.460
We read them.

12:31.682 --> 12:42.475
If we would do what the Lord wants us to do, we can't expect to live a sinful wicked life and never commune with the Lord.

12:42.556 --> 12:53.970
And then all of a sudden we need something and we're going to pray and we will expect God to do that because we have not been abiding in him in that situation.

12:55.426 --> 13:02.156
And I think that our prayer life will never be more effective than how much you understand the scriptures.

13:02.216 --> 13:06.923
The more you understand the Word of God, the more you know how to pray effectively.

13:08.165 --> 13:20.564
You see, a lot of times when I get ready to go to the Lord in prayer and I'm praying to the Lord, all of a sudden I remember something in the Word of God, the Holy Spirit brings to my remembrance something in the Word of God.

13:20.604 --> 13:24.370
And I can cling to that and I can say, yeah,

13:24.962 --> 13:27.445
Lord, I remember what your word said right here.

13:28.626 --> 13:34.293
And because your word said this, I know that you were able to do above and beyond.

13:35.975 --> 13:39.300
So it's good to have that scripture.

13:39.340 --> 13:40.701
You've got to have that word.

13:42.003 --> 13:48.931
And so when we think about that question that I asked you, does God promise to answer everyone's prayer?

13:49.592 --> 13:54.418
These are some of the things, some of the reasons why folks don't see answers to prayer.

13:54.946 --> 13:58.290
You never believe some of the things people tell me.

13:58.390 --> 14:01.794
I mean, they don't live, they don't live for Christ at all.

14:01.874 --> 14:03.396
You can tell it by their life.

14:04.777 --> 14:15.469
And then all of a sudden, they'll come to me and say, well, you know, I'm asking the good Lord up above to do this because I know the hell he's able to do it.

14:15.489 --> 14:17.712
Well, that's not the question why he's able to do it.

14:17.732 --> 14:19.614
What about your life?

14:19.634 --> 14:21.356
You're asking the Lord to do something.

14:21.376 --> 14:23.058
What about what's going on with you?

14:24.642 --> 14:27.747
There's no communion with the Lord.

14:28.928 --> 14:34.316
So we need to realize how many prayers, and here's another question.

14:34.396 --> 14:38.502
How many prayers do you and I have which we are still waiting for answers?

14:40.385 --> 14:42.148
I'm sure there are a lot of them.

14:43.189 --> 14:49.298
Folks, I've heard people tell me they prayed for something for years and years and years, and they're waiting for the answer.

14:51.714 --> 15:00.949
But I believe being honest before God will help us to apply this technique of examining ourselves.

15:01.229 --> 15:01.870
That's what I mean.

15:02.311 --> 15:05.676
If we're going to be honest, we've got to examine ourselves.

15:07.499 --> 15:10.343
Put us under the spotlight, Lord.

15:11.024 --> 15:12.447
What David said, search me.

15:14.189 --> 15:17.074
Psalm 66, 18, let's get that up there.

15:18.146 --> 15:25.073
Here's another reason, if I regard iniquity in my heart, look at this, the Lord will what?

15:25.093 --> 15:27.096
Not hear me.

15:27.116 --> 15:28.297
What's iniquity sin?

15:30.159 --> 15:30.559
Wrong.

15:31.801 --> 15:42.272
If I let that abide in my heart in my life, and I don't do anything about it, then I'm going to sit around and wait till next time I pray, I'm looking for the Lord to answer.

15:42.352 --> 15:43.893
Is he going to hear me?

15:43.954 --> 15:44.434
No.

15:45.090 --> 15:46.392
I tell you what he's going to hear.

15:46.592 --> 15:47.773
I tell you the prayer he's going to hear.

15:48.114 --> 15:49.876
He's going to hear that confession prayer.

15:50.156 --> 15:54.942
Lord, forgive me of the sin that's in my heart and in my life and cleansing me from it.

15:54.962 --> 16:02.872
He'll hear that prayer and then he'll wait to hear the next one you have because you're not no longer regarding iniquity.

16:04.414 --> 16:08.238
So there, there's a preference that we have to do.

16:09.139 --> 16:11.282
Look at Proverbs 28, 13.

16:13.282 --> 16:22.537
He that covereth his sins shall not prosper, but whosoever confesseth and forsakeeth them shall have mercy."

16:22.577 --> 16:23.158
Look at that.

16:24.760 --> 16:28.286
Can I cover up my sin and hope that the Lord never sees it?

16:29.007 --> 16:29.788
He sees all.

16:30.910 --> 16:31.932
There's no way to do that.

16:33.033 --> 16:36.379
Like Brother Dan told on King David last week.

16:36.819 --> 16:38.662
He's one of my favorite characters as well.

16:39.123 --> 16:41.106
David definitely sinned.

16:42.018 --> 16:45.823
But he said, you know what, I can't, I can't cover it up.

16:45.843 --> 16:47.406
I know the Lord knows what I did.

16:47.966 --> 16:53.634
And so we find David's great confession to the Lord for what he had did.

16:53.675 --> 16:54.916
He explained everything.

16:54.996 --> 16:58.902
He asked the Lord, please, cleanse me from that.

17:00.384 --> 17:01.886
And we have to do the same thing.

17:03.008 --> 17:04.109
We are all going to sin.

17:04.370 --> 17:10.258
We're all going to fall short, but don't try to cover it up with the Lord and then expect

17:10.882 --> 17:12.865
Hey, I got to go to Him and pray.

17:12.885 --> 17:14.767
I got a need that I need to pray for.

17:14.807 --> 17:18.633
I got something going on in my life, my family, and I need the Lord to move.

17:18.653 --> 17:21.577
And here we are over here with covered up sin.

17:23.079 --> 17:23.900
Get rid of that.

17:25.402 --> 17:26.924
Anyone who covers up their sins.

17:27.044 --> 17:28.086
And it's interesting.

17:29.347 --> 17:35.576
Did you know people decide that because of sin and equity in their heart, they try to justify it with the Lord?

17:35.876 --> 17:39.922
Well, Lord, I wouldn't have done that unless

17:40.866 --> 17:44.170
You would have sent something when it came my way or this would have been done.

17:44.531 --> 17:47.675
Oh, I was in that particular place or even blame somebody else.

17:47.735 --> 17:56.246
If somebody else hadn't had to pull me in there, if somebody else hadn't been doing the same thing, I wouldn't have done that Lord.

17:56.266 --> 18:02.394
We try to justify or blame someone else for the thing that's in our life.

18:04.276 --> 18:05.838
And it's not going to work with the Lord.

18:06.880 --> 18:08.722
We have to be willing.

18:08.930 --> 18:13.696
to confess to the Lord our sins, and then He will show us mercy.

18:14.777 --> 18:17.821
Look at 1 John 1, 8, and 9.

18:20.244 --> 18:25.731
If we say that we have no sin, let's just get that straight right now.

18:27.173 --> 18:28.855
Let's just clear that up.

18:28.935 --> 18:31.178
There's no need in saying that we have no sin.

18:32.199 --> 18:35.183
If we say we have no sin, who are we deceiving?

18:35.664 --> 18:37.426
We deceive ourselves.

18:38.114 --> 18:40.937
and the truth is not in us.

18:40.957 --> 18:50.626
But if we confess our sins, He's faithful just to forgive us our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.

18:50.946 --> 18:56.952
You see, there are folks walking around us saying, you know, I really don't feel like I'm that bad of a person.

18:56.972 --> 19:00.435
I really don't feel like I'm going to hear murdered nobody.

19:00.735 --> 19:01.896
I hadn't raped nobody.

19:02.297 --> 19:03.798
I hadn't stole from anybody.

19:04.098 --> 19:07.922
I'm good.

19:08.034 --> 19:09.276
We are not good.

19:10.077 --> 19:11.378
We have sinned it.

19:11.759 --> 19:12.900
It may be something we did.

19:12.960 --> 19:14.642
We don't even realize that we did.

19:14.682 --> 19:17.506
Why not go ahead and get those things under the blood?

19:18.888 --> 19:19.829
Get it confessed.

19:20.650 --> 19:23.514
Don't even go there and say, well, we don't have no sin.

19:24.335 --> 19:25.016
I'm not a sinner.

19:26.518 --> 19:28.340
The Bible says we deceive ourselves.

19:28.520 --> 19:33.106
So we have to ask the Lord to get things right.

19:33.410 --> 19:41.482
And this passage was written by the Apostle John and he was telling Christians what to do when sin overcomes him.

19:41.883 --> 19:47.311
And that's why I don't care how little the sin is, I don't care whether it's been along.

19:47.672 --> 19:54.122
The thing about sin is sin will gradually overcome a person.

19:54.142 --> 19:58.428
It'll overcome their testimony, it'll overcome their joy, it'll overcome them.

19:58.449 --> 20:02.034
They won't want to come to church after a while and they certainly quit playing.

20:03.778 --> 20:09.204
It's a thing that just works on us and we need to realize that.

20:11.426 --> 20:15.050
So we need to confess that sin, get it out of the way.

20:15.091 --> 20:23.540
And you know, I want to say there's a big difference between being sorry and being repentant.

20:23.560 --> 20:32.690
Some folks are just sorry because they got caught, sorry because someone else found out, but it's a different thing.

20:32.962 --> 20:36.387
when we come to that realize, hey, I know our sin.

20:36.907 --> 20:37.989
I know I need to repent.

20:38.289 --> 20:39.591
I've got to get it covered.

20:39.611 --> 20:40.953
I've got to get it taken care of.

20:42.615 --> 20:47.161
And so we realize that sin will break you down.

20:48.322 --> 20:52.488
It will affect you in many ways and probably other people around you as well.

20:54.290 --> 20:58.296
So let's just be honest and have an honest heart.

20:58.736 --> 21:02.962
And if you, if you'll do that before you go to the Lord in prayer,

21:04.674 --> 21:05.655
have an honest heart.

21:06.116 --> 21:09.579
Then when you get ready to pray, you'll be ready to pray.

21:10.380 --> 21:12.062
Because you've gotten everything out of the way.

21:13.604 --> 21:17.188
And then when we go back to that pray with our season, don't just wait.

21:19.250 --> 21:22.574
You say, well, I need to, I'm going to be praying about that Tuesday.

21:23.214 --> 21:24.956
